observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:

Adhere to the general process in handling and accounting for PPE prescribed in Manual on the New Government Accounting System in order to strengthen the internal control of the agency;

Require the General Services Officer (GSO) and the Municipal Accountant to maintain Property Cards and Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards (PPELC), respectively; 

Create an Inventory Committee and regularly conduct an Annual Physical Inventory and reconcile the same with accounting records to determine any discrepancy; 

Continue the issuance of Property Acknowledgment Receipt (PAR) for all succeeding purchases and issuances of Equipment and for all PPE that were already issued but no PAR was issued which is essential for control and monitoring of the property.

We recommended that Management:
Adhere to the general process in handling and accounting for PPE prescribed in Manual on the New Government Accounting System in order to strengthen the internal control of the agency;
Require the Municipal Treasurer and the Municipal Accountant to maintain Property Cards and Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards (PPELC), respectively;
Regularly conduct an Annual Physical Inventory and reconcile the same with accounting records to determine any discrepancy;
Continue the issuance of Property Acknowledgment Receipt (PAR) for all succeeding purchases and issuances of Equipment and for all PPEs that were already issued but no PAR was issued to them which is essential for the control and monitoring of the property; and
Designate a General Services Officer (GSO) who is not assigned as an Accounting Staff who will independently perform the duties of a GSO.

We recommended that Management:
Instruct the personnel concerned to regularly conduct an Annual Physical Inventory and reconcile the same with the records of the accounting and the Municipal Treasurer;
Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to regularly prepare the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) and forward to Accounting Unit to serve as basis in the preparation of JEV and recording of issuances;
Require the Accounting unit to account for the inventories using the perpetual inventory method and maintain supply ledger cards;
Require the Municipal Treasurer to maintain stock cards and record deliveries and issuances therein;
Adhere to the general process in handling and accounting for Inventories and Supplies and Materials prescribed in Manual on the New Government Accounting System in order to strengthen the internal control of the agency; and
Purchase supplies and materials needed for the quarter based on the approved annual procurement program, at the beginning of the year and of each subsequent quarters thru public bidding pursuant to Republic Act No 9184 and its IRR.

We recommended that Management:
Require the Municipal Accountant to exert all effort to locate/retrieve the supporting documents and ledgers of the dormant accounts and conduct an in-depth analysis of these accounts so that settlement could be made and adjustments, if necessary, could be effected in the books;
In case all possible remedies fail, comply with the requirements in requesting for write-off of the dormant accounts as prescribed by the above-cited COA Circular.

We recommended that  the Local Chief Executive:

•  	Consider adopting the Payroll-thru-bank system to strengthen internal control, particularly in the safeguarding of its Payroll Fund and to promote operational efficiency;

•	Coordinate with the chosen servicing bank of the municipality for Automated Teller Machine (ATM) service.securing comprehensive insurance.

